#compdef SecretScanner
# =============================================================================
# SecretScanner — Deepfence's "find secrets and passwords in
#                  container images and file systems" — a Go
#                  binary that scans local filesystems, mounted
#                  hosts, Docker images, containers, and
#                  Kubernetes pods for accidentally-committed
#                  secrets (AWS keys, API tokens, private SSH
#                  keys, GitHub tokens, OpenAI keys, database
#                  passwords, JWT secrets, etc).  Uses YARA
#                  RULES + REGEX SIGNATURES for pattern matching
#                  with severity classification (low/medium/
#                  high/critical).  Distinguishing features:
#                    - Container image scanning via Docker
#                      Remote API (no Docker daemon required —
#                      pulls layers via OCI registry)
#                    - Live host scanning via bind-mounted
#                      filesystem
#                    - Multiple output formats: table (default
#                      for terminal), JSON (for CI/CD pipelines),
#                      gRPC plugin mode (for Deepfence
#                      ThreatMapper integration)
#                    - Fail-on-count thresholds for CI gating
#                      (fail build if N+ secrets found, with
#                      severity-specific gates)
#                    - YaraHunter integration for shared YARA
#                      rule + signature update mechanism
#                  Used at scale in CI/CD pipelines + Kubernetes
#                  admission controllers + container registry
#                  scanning workflows for AWS/GCP/Azure cloud
#                  deployments.
#
# Author:  Deepfence Inc. (San Francisco/Bangalore — cloud-
#          native security platform company) — Manish Bhatt +
#          Sreemoyee Sengupta + Deepfence team.  SecretScanner
#          is part of Deepfence's ThreatMapper open-source
#          cloud-native runtime threat detection platform.
# Source:  https://github.com/deepfence/SecretScanner
#          https://github.com/deepfence/SecretScanner/blob/main/main.go
#          https://github.com/deepfence/SecretScanner/blob/main/core/options.go
